pageContext.claim: “Think of that and African-American, Hispanic-American, and Asian-American unemployment rates have reached the lowest levels in history.”
pageContext.analysis: The Asian-American statistic has been around for less than 20 years. And while it reached a low of 2.0 percent rate in May 2018, it rose to 2.8 percent in September, the most recent month available. Lately, Trump has been using the word "reached," perhaps to indicate the lows are in the past.
